This paper presents a study on the channel model parameters for millimeter-wave communication, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of 3GPP modeling parameters, which is related to communication systems (cs.COMM) and system engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper presents empirical measurements and modeling techniques for small-scale and large-scale channel parameters, which is related to millimeter-wave communication (cs.MM).
